         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">5/8/78. ¶  ¶ I am glad, dear Dr Hector, that you are pleased with the English by me enlarged edition of Wittsteins work. ¶  It has been a heavy toil &amp; great expense to me; the printing cost about £250...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">78.08.05</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">To James Hector</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">MU 94, box 4 (3579), Museum of New Zealand Te Papa Tongarewa, Wellington.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">5/8/78.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I am glad, dear Dr Hector, that you are pleased with the English by me enlarged edition of Wittsteins work.<note xml:id="ftn1" type="footnote" n="1">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Wittstein (1878), i.e. B78.06.09.</p>
               </note> It has been a heavy toil &amp; great expense to me; the printing cost about £250, and I fear I shall not cover one fourth of that outlay by sale. Your principal medical men ought to purchase the work. Of course the book will greatly facilitate your own researches, as it brings together all that is known til date in this direction for comparison; besides Wittsteins method of analyzing is the result of half a centurys exertions. Could you not review the work in a local journal, to bring it there into notice </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Only one vol. of the Institute is missing here.<note xml:id="ftn2" type="footnote" n="2">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>See M to J. Hector, 1 August 1878.</p>
               </note> Kirk's compilation,<note xml:id="ftn3" type="footnote" n="3">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Kirk (1878).</p>
               </note> (I think made on my suggestion) gives an opportunity of easily finding out, what has been added since Hookers Handbook<note xml:id="ftn4" type="footnote" n="4">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>J. Hooker (1864-7).</p>
               </note> appeared. Best thanks for the "New Zealand grasses"<note xml:id="ftn5" type="footnote" n="5">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <seg style="">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
                     </seg>Curl (1878) and/or Curl (1879), if the latter, read on 17 August 1878, <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>was available and sent as a preprint.</p>
               </note>
            </p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">Regardfully</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Ferd. von Mueller</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">Prof Kirk sent me years ago a solitary flower of a <name key="Brasenia">Brasenia</name> (or <name key="Hydropeltis">Hydropeltis</name>) from the Waikatoo or Wangenui River;<note xml:id="ftn6" type="footnote" n="6">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Waikato and Wanganui rivers, NZ.</p>
               </note> how can I get a complete plant for comparison with the australian species. As the flower is rather showy, there ought to be no difficulty to get a specimen of this water plant.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Should you in using my translation derive great benefit from it in your laboratory, then say in the record a kind word of credit, as it will be a support to me in my "struggle for existence".<note xml:id="ftn7" type="footnote" n="7">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>The title of ch. 3 of Darwin (1859).</p>
               </note>
            </p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="plant%20names" xml:lang="en">
               <name key="Brasenia">Brasenia</name>
            </p>
            <p rend="plant%20names" xml:lang="en">
               <name key="Hydropeltis">Hydropeltis</name>
            </p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
         </div>
